description: Acupuncture Excellence - David Thorpe MBAcC LicAc 4 de setembro de 2019 · If you have an autoimmune condition, such as coeliac disease, type 1 diabetes, rheumatoid arthritis, Crohn’s disease, multiple sclerosis, lupus, ulcerative colitis or psoriasis, would you like to come along to my “Reversing Autoimmunity” talk on Wednesday 2nd October in Potten End? In 2017, our 6-year-old son was diagnosed with an autoimmune disorder which required urgent medical treatment at Great Ormond Street hospital. Overwhelmed by his odds of chronic kidney disease an...d possible lifelong medication, I immersed myself in the latest science of how the immune system works, and sought help to apply what I learned until his condition was fully reversed. In this talk, I would love to share leading edge research into the causes of autoimmunity with you; explaining how the food we eat, how the chemicals we’re exposed to, and how the stress we’re under lead to illness; and how we can reverse inflammation by addressing imbalances within our minds and bodies. By sharing our story, I hope to inspire you to take back control of your own health, or that of a loved one, using one or more of the approaches which I outline in this talk. If you’re interested, please contact me on 07958 223 836 (or annettebowles@hotmail.com) for further details and to reserve a place. Ver mais

name: California Sandwiches York Mills
description: The Severino Family proudly serving the Woodbridge community Fine Italian Sandwiches and Salads for 15yrs. We use only Fresh All Natural Ingredients. Additional Information California Sandwiches was born in Toronto’s Little Italy. During the mid 1960’s, the Papa/Bertucci family purchased a local grocery store with the hope of sup...porting a growing family. They quickly discovered they had something special when customers were coming for lunch instead of groceries. As the popularity of their homemade sandwiches grew, they decided to jump on the opportunity. In 1967 the first California Sandwiches was born. From its inception as “La Rinacente”, the veal sandwich quickly became one of Toronto’s favorites. Today, very little has changed. There are now 12 locations, all family owned and operated. Traditional methods of food preparation are still in practice. Each store has its own butcher and the meat is cut on site. Only the finest in Italian tomatoes are ground for our sauce that is made fresh daily. Our kaiser buns are baked by an Italian bakery and delivered every morning. And our cheeses and produce are bought and prepared for use as needed. Quality food and attention to detail have kept this business strong and valued.
